OL,3,CJohn Swinney calls on parties to agree
OL,4,Cbudget quickly
OL,6,FThe First Minister refused to say how
OL,7,Fthe money would be deployed, but was
OL,8,Fclear he has been presented with
OL,9,Fmultiple options, adding: "The choices
OL,10,Fand the prioritisation is under way
OL,11,Fjust now, but the absolute commitment
OL,12,Fis there that the resources that we
OL,13,Fwould have spent on lifting the two-
OL,14,Fchild limit will be in place to
OL,15,Fsupport other measures to reduce child
OL,16,Fpoverty."
