OL,3,CJohn Swinney calls on parties to agree
OL,4,Cbudget quickly
OL,6,FSpeaking to PA, Scottish Tory leader
OL,7,FRussell Findlay said the price of his
OL,8,Fparty's support would be, at least,
OL,9,Faligning income taxes in Scotland with
OL,10,Fthe rest of the UK.
OL,12,FBut the First Minister did not seem
OL,13,Fwilling to cut taxes, saying: "I think
OL,14,Fsome of the points that are advanced
OL,15,Fby the Conservatives are not aligned
OL,16,Fwith our principles and our
OL,17,Fprogrammes, but we'll talk to them to
OL,18,Fsee what progress can be made."
